# Code Quality Rules

## Complexity

- Maximum cyclomatic complexity: 7 (35 for .tsx files)
- Cognitive complexity is enforced via SonarJS

## Console Statements

- Only `console.warn`, `console.error`, `console.info` are allowed
- `console.log` is prohibited

## Null vs Undefined

- Prefer `undefined` over `null`
- `undefined` = missing and not declared
- `null` = missing but declared (use only when part of API)

## Formatting

- Use Prettier for code formatting
- Use tabs for indentation (not spaces)
- Use single quotes for JS/TS strings
- Use double quotes for JSX/HTML attributes
- Always use semicolons
